The paper proposes a new type of neuron that can be easily implemented into neural networks and enhances their performance. This suggests that the paper belongs to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the theoretical implications of adding the amplifying neuron to the hidden layer, which falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the performance assessments of neural networks, which is a common topic in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the numerical experiments conducted to verify the effectiveness of the proposed neurons, which could fall under the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category.
